Bootstrap is a css framework used for responsive websites
its a grid based system with each page divided in 12 columns
lg- large screens(big tvs, projectors)
md- medium devices(laptops, PC's)
sm- small devices(tablets, phablets)
xs- extra small devices(smartphones)

in nested columns each new division again is considered to have 12 columns
<div class="col-md-4"> </div>
<div class="col-md-8">
  <div class="col-md-12">
    <div class="col-md-6"> </div>
    <div class="col-md-6"> </div>
   </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row"> optional

  <div class="container">: leaves certain space to the left and right and shows content in the center


  Classes for button -  btn is a default class for designing
  button sizes = btn-lg, btn-sm, btn-xs. btn-md being default
  button color = btn-primary, btn-warning, btn-danger, btn-success, btn-info

  eg. btn btn-xs btn-danger

  btn-block fills all the available columns with the button
  
